🔍 LAD: Log Anomaly Detector
LAD is a lightweight, high-performance security tool written in Rust. It uses Unsupervised Machine Learning to parse server logs and automatically detect suspicious behavior without any pre-defined rules.

🚀 Technical Features
Zero-Copy Parsing: Uses Rust's memory safety to scan logs at near-native speeds.

K-Means Intelligence: Automatically groups traffic into "Normal" and "Suspicious" clusters using the linfa ML framework.

Resource Efficient: Designed to run on low-resource VMs or edge servers with minimal CPU/RAM impact.

Type-Safe Data: Every log line is validated and transformed into a structured format before analysis.

🛠️ Installation & Usage
1. Requirements
Rust 1.80 or newer.

2. Setup

cd log-guardian-rs
cargo run
